<paragraph role="heading" id="par_idN10557" xml-lang="en-US" level="1" l10n="NEW"><link href="text/shared/02/basicshapes.xhp">Basic Shapes</link></paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_idN10567" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW"><ahelp hid=".">Opens the Basic Shapes toolbar which you can use to insert graphics into your document.</ahelp></paragraph>
</section>
<section id="howtoget">
<embed href="text/shared/00/00000404.xhp#sybasicshapes"/>
</section>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_idN10591" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW">Click an icon on the Basic Shapes toolbar, and then drag in the document to draw the shape.</paragraph>
<paragraph role="note" id="par_idN10594" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW">Some shapes have a handle which you can drag to change the properties of the shape. The mouse pointer changes to a hand symbol over these special handles.</paragraph>
